The paper deals with video-based face recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of probabilistic Multi-Region Histograms and clustering techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between computational efficiency and recognition accuracy, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the experiments involve evaluating different face selection metrics, which could be considered information retrieval (cs.IR).
